Expansion performed internally based on codesystem NG-Imm Adverse Event Clinical Status CS v0.5.0 (CodeSystem)

This value set contains 6 concepts

CodeSystemDisplay (en-US)Definition
  activehttps://nphcda.gov.ng/immunizationIG/CodeSystem/nigeria-clinical-statusActiveThe clinical condition is currently present, ongoing, or requires active management or monitoring.
  inactivehttps://nphcda.gov.ng/immunizationIG/CodeSystem/nigeria-clinical-statusInactiveThe clinical condition is no longer present but is not considered resolved; it may recur or requires no current treatment.
  resolvedhttps://nphcda.gov.ng/immunizationIG/CodeSystem/nigeria-clinical-statusResolvedThe clinical condition has completely resolved and is no longer impacting the patient's health or requiring further management.
  recoveredhttps://nphcda.gov.ng/immunizationIG/CodeSystem/nigeria-clinical-statusRecoveredThe individual has recovered fully from the adverse event without any long-term effects or sequelae.
  recovered-with-sequelaehttps://nphcda.gov.ng/immunizationIG/CodeSystem/nigeria-clinical-statusRecovered with sequelaeThe individual has recovered from the adverse event but with lasting effects, complications, or disabilities.
  deathhttps://nphcda.gov.ng/immunizationIG/CodeSystem/nigeria-clinical-statusDeathThe adverse event resulted in the death of the individual.
